# USB device allowlist for usb-monitor.
# Format: one VID:PID per line, lowercase hex, no spaces.
# Comments (#) and blank lines are ignored.
#
# Entries below this header are seeded from `lsusb` at install time
# (all devices currently connected when the monitor was set up).
#
# To trust a new device after install, append its VID:PID:
#   echo '046d:c52b' | sudo tee -a /var/lib/usb-monitor/allow
#
# To find VID:PID of an unknown device:
#   lsusb
